            . I am a Police-officer. The prisoner was<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183110200054"></xptr>given into my custody on the 14th of September - I asked what she had been doing; she said Nothing - I asked for her purse; she said she had lost it the evening before - I then searched, and found it in a hat-box in her bed-room, with fourteen duplicates in it; she then said she was very sorry, but she must own she had taken the things.</p>
